1 of 2, because I don't know how to brevity...

Appreciate the feedback! I was worried that their coming down and aftercare might have been a little rushed, and looking back through it just now, I'm spitting a couple grammar mistakes and awkward phrasings I might need to correct. Still, I'm starting to realize that I have a habit of leaving too much unsaid it contextual (like with Maggie's paranoia over dinner in TWTH). I'll work on that in the future.

As to what's going on at the end, I wanted to play up the head games that someone typically has to deal with after something that stressful. At least in my experience when you go through a really intense sexual experience, your fears and doubts tend to come back at you hard afterwards. While what Dylan and Julie did was fairly normal for an experienced kinky couple, it was - in my mind, at least - meant to be WAAAAY too much, way too fast. It'd be akin to that feeling when you jerk it to something extreme, then feel dirty after you nut... only on space crack.

As to the specifics of their odd behavior afterwards? I had cast Julie as a bit of an 'adorable sperg', who absolutely got off on the IDEA of excitement and danger, but who had/has near crippling social anxiety. One of her biggest fears across the story was being singled out or publicly embarrassed, especially sexually (hence the meltdown in the clubhouse changing room). The pics - which she asked Dylan to take - were meant to be her 'dragon' to slay, and a metaphor for her giving herself fully to him. ... Unsurprisingly (or so I'd thought) it was also what she fixated hard on when the post coital crash hit.

Part 2 of 2

Dylan is your typical mech/aero engineer in that he's sociable, if a bit socially inept. Throughout, his personal tastes were fairly vanilla, though his biggest turn-on was the control of being able to get Julie ridiculously wound up /making her cum hard. It's why he went along with their public play their first Christmas together, and it's how he talked himself into the fairly extreme BDSM session. The whole time he's playing the Dom, he's fighting with his conscience and his baser urges.

Like many engineers, he's a compulsive 'fixer', making big, if clumsy, gestures for Julie whenever she's feeling down or has a problem. It's why he set up their ill conceived and arguably unnecessary role play at the banquet hall, why he backed out of Christmas dinner to care for her the first time around, why he flippantly offers to delete all the photos (ironically, the opposite of what Julie wanted), and why he just blurted out the offer to move in together (though that would eventually might as well have been assumed).

As to what was going on the last few paragraphs? When Julie tells him why she wants him to keep the photos, he finally gets why she wanted him to take them in the first place, and just how much of herself she was giving to him. Between the impact of the realization and the mental stress of (reluctantly) Dom'ing and the impact of her gift, he had broken and was crying into her shoulder. The idea was to close on a cute little scene where Julie, the self conscious sub, was the one consoling her outwardly confident Dom.
